olive oil
1 bag baby broccoli
½ lemon
1 bag baby spinach leaves
1 packet pork loin steaks
1 packet Herb & Mushroom Seasoning
½ bottle cream
1 packet mashed potato
1 bag parsley

• Halve any thick baby broccoli stalks
lengthways. Slice lemon in half
• In a frying pan, heat a drizzle of olive
oil over medium-high heat. Cook
baby broccoli until tender, 5-6 mins
• Remove from heat, add spinach and
cook until wilted. Transfer to a bowl
and cover to keep warm

• Return pan to medium-high heat with
a drizzle of oil
• Season pork loin on each side. Cook
pork until cooked through, 3-4 mins
each side
• Reduce heat to low, add herb
seasoning, cream (1/2 bottle for 2P
/ 1 bottle for 4P), a squeeze of lemon
juice, and a splash of water. Cook,
stirring, until slightly reduced,
1-2 minutes. Season

• Meanwhile, transfer mashed potato
to a heatproof bowl. Microwave until
hot and steaming, 3 mins. Season
to taste
• Plate up mash, pork and greens
• Pour over creamy sauce. Tear over
parsley to serve